HTML: HyperText Markup Language
- Anatomy of an HTML Tag:
<h1></h1> tag omission is None
<br> <hr> self-closing tag: must not have an end tag

- HTML Attribute
<hr size="3" noshade>
hr: HTML element
size="3": HTML Attribute
align / color / noshade / size/ width

<center>
</center>

- comment:
<!-- ...... -->

- <title>Name shown on tag</title> 

- HTML <meta> Tag 
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="description" content="Free Web tutorials">  : tells the search engine what to show
  <meta name="keywords" content="HTML,CSS,XML,JavaScript">
  <meta name="author" content="John Doe">
</head>

- italicize and bold
always use <em></em> <strong></strong>

- list
<ul></ul> unordered list
<ol></ol> ordered list
<li></li> each bullet points in a list
<ul>
  <li>xxx</li>
  <li>ooo</li>
</ul>

- image :self-closing tag
<img src="..." alt="image content">

- Anchor tag, not self closing
<a href="https://...">Hello</a>
a: html element
href: attribute
Hello: link text, highlighted text
can link other pages or external source
for download: <a download href="https://...">Download</a>

https://web.stanford.edu/group/csp/cs21/htmlcheatsheet.pdf


- Table
<table>
  <thead>     <!--can be omitted-->
    <tr>
      <th></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td></td> #table data
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

- Form: form,lable,input(self-closing)
<form class="" action="mailto:syche55@gmail.com" method="post" enctype="text/plain">
      <label>Your Name:</label>
      <input type="text" name="yourName" value=""><br>
      <label>Your Message:</label><br>
      <textarea name="yourMessage" rows="10" cols="50"></textarea><br>
      <input type="submit" name="">
</form>
    <form class="" action="index.html" method="post">
      <input type="text" name="" value="">
      <input type="password" name="" value=""> encrypted
      <input type="submit" name="" value="">
      <input type="file" name="" value="">
      <input type="date" name="" value="">
      <input type="radio" name="" value="">
      <input type="range" name="" value="">
</form>
